OVERVIEW

L13 is a language with text layout semantics. It translates L9 into a list of
node representing tokens of a language. Each node includes a string of text and
a column and line number. L13 code is used to drive the dynamic layout of code
on a virtual or physical canvas.

L13 is written in L0. 

BUILDING

To build:

   cd build
   ./make.sh

This produces the file:

   ../bin/l13c.swf


USING

To run:

    ./comp.sh some.l9

or

    avmshell ../bin/l13c.swf some.l9

where avmshell is the name of a recent build of Tamarin.

This produces the file:

    some.l9.l13

